<br>
What I was doing was sitting in the middle of a bunch of spiders that were non aggro and had a mix of greens and yellows.  I would charm a green send it to yellow, wait until the green was at half health then start flinging arrows.  The outcome would be me not getting hit and the green mob at about 10% health.  The other option I could use would be me taking aggro right away and tanking.  This would end with me at 10% health (not good) and the spider at full health.<br>
<br>
Now the real problem is that NPC mobs regain health VERY slow, I can gain health 2 to 3 times faster than a mob.  My thinking is that mobs gain health at the same rate as PC's that are standing.  So if there are an abundance of greens around which there was in this case, I would usually cycle between them.  Charm green1, attack yellow, release geen1, charm green2, attack yellow, release green2, charm green3, attack yellow, release green3, repeat from begining, charm green1.<br>
<br>
Granted I could have kept that one spider but I would have gained exp at 1/3 the rate, which most people would rather not do.  However, if someone would have said something to me I personallly would have stopped.  <br>
<br>
Again, I am glad you brought this topic up because I never thought of the impact it could have on others.  Also though please know that what the people are doing are just trying to level as fast and efficiently as possible.  Although I will agree that should never be done at the expense of others.<br>
<br>
Ezekiell/Atton <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showMessage?topicID=347.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showMessage?topicID=327.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=343.topic&index=3><img src=http://dancingdruid.homestead.com/files/add.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.threadControl?topicID=343.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=343.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=343.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub15.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="daggersincamelotfrm24">General<option value="daggersincamelotfrm1">DAoC General<option value="daggersincamelotfrm23">Announcements<option value="daggersincamelotfrm2">Events<option value="daggersincamelotfrm4">Trade Skills<option value="daggersincamelotfrm3">In Game Quests<option value="daggersincamelotfrm5">Treasury<option value="daggersincamelotfrm17">Game Mechanic Discussions<option value="daggersincamelotfrm26">Looking For Group<option value="daggers